HEADWORD: Corticifer
<hw>Cor*tic"i*fer</hw> <pr>(k?r-t?s"?-f?r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of the <suborder>Gorgoniacea</suborder>; --
so called because the fleshy part surrounds a solid axis, like a
bark.</def>⟦br⟧
